      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T06:13:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "File names containing timestamps are a bit harder to locate. It\u0027s nice to avoid it unless we create many of them in the same directory.\n\nInstead I recommend creating a top directory whose name contains a timestamp, and creating a fixed-name file underneath it, just like Tast CLI do (e.g. /tmp/tast/results/YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS/full.txt)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 29,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "3c38b72f398d473fa58abfbb0282161bbaba3cc3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
