      "writtenOn": "2020-12-07T06:13:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "fullLog is leaked (log.New does not close it). Also it\u0027s a bit difficult to debug if logs are not printed to stderr.\n\nI recommend using the default configuration (printing to stderr) for now. Later we can extend it to print logs to both stderr and a file. For example, you can use io.MultiWriter for this purpose.\nhttps://godoc.org/io#MultiWriter",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 32,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "3c38b72f398d473fa58abfbb0282161bbaba3cc3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
